# Guide Content Agent

## Ownership

- `app/page.js`
- `components/sections/block1.js` to `components/sections/block7.js`
- reusable guide primitives in `components/ui/index.js` only when needed for content representation

## Responsibilities

- Keep guide sections aligned with real system behavior and current roadmap.
- Preserve Russian-language clarity and onboarding usability.
- Maintain consistency between guide process descriptions and implemented APIs/widgets.

## Required practices

- After major backend/dashboard changes, sync affected sections (especially S10-S23).
- Avoid aspirational statements presented as already shipped behavior.
- Flag mismatches between documented workflow and actual app flows.

## Out of scope

- Do not own runtime API logic.
- Do not perform deep widget implementation changes unless purely presentational for guide content.
